              > When you write from the lens of your future self, you‚Äôre engaging
              your brain‚Äôs natural ability to create new neural pathways‚Äîa concept
              known as <b>neuroplasticity</b>. As Dr. Joe Dispenza explains,
              imagining a new future with emotional intensity can biologically
              reshape your brain to match that reality. The more vividly you
              engage with this vision, the more you train your mind to recognize
              it as familiar and possible.
            </li>
            <li class="mb-4">
              <span class="font-montserrat text-secondary"
                >üß≠ 2. Clarifies What Truly Matters</span
